Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.43,0:00:04.31,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Alibis, codes, cases, deals.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.31,0:00:07.02,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The mysterious Black Organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.02,0:00:07.77,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today's the conclusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.77,0:00:10.48,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The criminal and trick appear like magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.48,0:00:11.98,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.98,0:00:13.98,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.98,0:00:16.74,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.17,0:02:02.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran and Sonoko went to a mountain lodge on a meeting of magic fans that met via the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.12,0:02:00.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the mountain lodge was isolated,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.38,0:02:06.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and a second victim's body was found in the middle of a snowfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.39,0:02:07.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}However, their board leader, Tsutomu Nishiyama{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}, was killed in his apartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.17,0:02:12.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There were no footprints around the body: An impossible crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.43,0:02:12.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and furthermore, a creepy message was left at the scene pointing at it being a serial murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.65,0:02:15.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The bridge, which was the only link to the outside world, had been set on fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.89,0:02:19.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Was it done by the missing member, the Shadow Priest?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.44,0:02:24.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see! That's how it was!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.90,0:02:29.49,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now I know how the impossible crime's trick was done.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.49,0:02:34.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And I know the killer's identity, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.88,0:02:48.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So, where should I begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.76,0:02:50.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.68,0:02:52.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't play with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.76,0:02:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right. It's just one bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.39,0:03:01.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Do you have a stapler, scissors and a large rope in this lodge that I could borrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.61,0:03:04.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you want those things for?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.44,0:03:08.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to wait here until the morning when the police arrive, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.99,0:03:13.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I'm bored, I figured I could do some crafts. {lit. "drawing and manual arts."}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.32,0:03:17.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I have all that in my room. Let's go get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.37,0:03:19.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.37,0:03:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.21,0:03:25.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here. That's everything you asked for.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.29,0:03:26.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.75,0:03:30.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, do you have some drawing paper and crayons?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.47,0:03:36.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have the drawing paper but... I don't think I have crayons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.81,0:03:40.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy, I found some color pencils.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.23,0:03:41.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.73,0:03:45.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bo... Boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.36,0:03:48.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.82,0:03:51.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I lost sight of him just for a bit and...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.78,0:03:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he went to the restroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.45,0:04:02.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I checked and he wasn't there. And the arrow from the bow-gun I was looking after is gone too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.71,0:04:04.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.04,0:04:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tha... That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.63,0:04:09.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the killer went after the kid and... {literally "maybe that boy... the killer..." but that sentence is incomplete and would get the order switched in a translation -- this is the closest approximation I can get that makes sense, keeps every word in the original, and is still incomplete}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.55,0:04:15.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just now, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.26,0:04:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right. Let's all go look for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.39,0:04:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.23,0:04:24.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.40,0:04:28.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.69,0:04:32.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.78,0:04:36.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Again...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.16,0:04:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's somebody out there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.04,0:04:42.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This time it came from the woods on the right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.83,0:04:44.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.04,0:04:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.46,0:04:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.88,0:04:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.68,0:05:03.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez! Always doing stupid dangerous things!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.02,0:05:05.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing, going after the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.44,0:05:10.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if the killer got the bow-gun back, then that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.69,0:05:13.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we loiter around here, we'll all be targets!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.24,0:05:17.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It worked great, huh, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.07,0:05:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? What did?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.58,0:05:23.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, that thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.04,0:05:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.33,0:05:25.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.55,0:05:34.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.93,0:05:37.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? Snap out of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.64,0:05:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the one who needs to snap out of it, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.06,0:05:47.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, go and pick up the bow-gun behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.81,0:05:48.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.56,0:05:51.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the bow-gun doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.44,0:05:55.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then take it to the middle room on the left side, Hamano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.15,0:05:56.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.74,0:05:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.95,0:06:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran and I are going to be reconstructing the bloody magic show that the killer gave us tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.92,0:06:13.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Reconstructing the bloody magic show?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.38,0:06:17.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does this mean you figured it out? The impossible crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.13,0:06:20.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. How the killer got Hamano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.14,0:06:23.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to the center of the backyard without leaving any footprints in the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.85,0:06:27.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And of course, who did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.90,0:06:32.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say? You know who the killer is?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.19,0:06:36.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, Ran. Go and take the bow-gun to Hamano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room on the left side.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.78,0:06:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I already have everything ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.70,0:06:41.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.66,0:06:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what are you going to do with the bow-gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.00,0:06:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need not only the bow-gun, but also scissors and some rope to perform the impossible crime. {literally " to make this impossible crime possible"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.05,0:06:58.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, we make a small hole in the ends of two of the arrows in the bow-gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.97,0:07:03.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and we pass some strings through those holes, knotting them to make two small loops.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.30,0:07:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then pass the a previously measured long string through the two loops.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.14,0:07:13.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tie two more strings to the center of that large one,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.31,0:07:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Make those strings' ends into loops, tie them to the railings of the veranda, and then everything's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.40,0:07:23.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, you only have to fire the arrows one by one with the bow-gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.66,0:07:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.66,0:07:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I set up the arrows like you drew on the paper!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.08,0:07:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But where do I aim?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.00,0:07:34.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Near this tree, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.42,0:07:39.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry! If you miss you can try again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.30,0:07:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Make sure the strings don't twist together!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.68,0:07:46.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'm gonna fire! Everybody stand back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.10,0:07:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here we go...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.14,0:07:50.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.10,0:07:53.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me shoot instead. I'm pretty good at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.90,0:07:56.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That guy! When'd he get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.44,0:07:59.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that all right, Detective Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.11,0:08:00.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.36,0:08:03.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then here it goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.87,0:08:06.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.91,0:08:10.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be so pleased when you still have another arrow to fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.71,0:08:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now fire to the base of the tree on the other side of the one you just shot at.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.25,0:08:25.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The shape these strings form is like two sails in the mast of a yacht.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.14,0:08:27.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.35,0:08:30.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? You still don't understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.14,0:08:33.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, Doitō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Use the {\i1}futon{\i0} like a body,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.89,0:08:36.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and into the small ring of the string tied around it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.61,0:08:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,pass one end of one of the two strings making up the yacht's mast.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.53,0:08:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finally, drop the {\i1}futon{\i0} from the veranda as if it was a ropeway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.54,0:08:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body is, as you can see, in the center of the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.50,0:08:54.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I... I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.12,0:08:55.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.75,0:09:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can take the body without leaving a single footprint like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.00,0:09:05.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can pass the string through a hole in the belt, and you get a ropeway!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.68,0:09:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly. The killer used the bow-gun to have the garden's empty air support a ropeway,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.93,0:09:16.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and so for just a moment, turned the impossible into possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.39,0:09:16.60,Signs,,0,0,0,,Support Point
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.90,0:09:20.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did he get rid of all that evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.78,0:09:28.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he'd pulled the ropes, he'd have left an odd track in the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.03,0:09:32.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was nothing like that on the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.33,0:09:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about that. Come on, Doitō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Tie the other string making up the mast to another arrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.04,0:09:43.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and fire it in the air above whichever side of the woods you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.96,0:09:47.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the same time untie the ropes in the veranda!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.59,0:09:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once you have, all remaining questions will be answered!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.73,0:10:01.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.90,0:10:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way he gets rid of the strings without touching the snow around the body, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.24,0:10:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.41,0:10:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But aren't the arrows still stuck to the tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.16,0:10:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the killer burned the bridge and trapped us here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.50,0:10:23.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To retrieve the arrows before the police came.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.21,0:10:24.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.67,0:10:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kikue Tanaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the killer!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.85,0:10:34.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Conan Episode 134\NThe Amateur Magician Murder Case (Case Closed)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.49,0:10:37.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tanaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s the killer, you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.87,0:10:39.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.54,0:10:43.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.54,0:10:47.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer tried to take my life with the bow-gun, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.38,0:10:50.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you say I'm the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.30,0:10:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can even ask Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, who was with me at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.22,0:11:00.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. You set that up on purpose in order to get out of the suspect list!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.72,0:11:02.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did I do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.64,0:11:04.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a simple trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.64,0:11:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You stapled the wall above the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.11,0:11:10.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,passed a string through it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.40,0:11:13.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,attaching a weight to a suitable position along it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.19,0:11:16.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then passing the remaining string between the pillars of the floor above
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.91,0:11:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and beneath the window and into your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.41,0:11:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you tied it to your bed, and covered it with some clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.79,0:11:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While pretending to pick up your clothes, by just cutting the string,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.37,0:11:30.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the glass in the window would break by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.09,0:11:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, as you felt the glass break,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.96,0:11:36.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you used the bow-gun you'd hidden under the clothes to fire over your shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.93,0:11:39.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And while Ran and the others were looking at the arrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.47,0:11:43.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you picked up the string again, raising the weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.14,0:11:48.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and opened the curtains to show them the glass was broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.27,0:11:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, you can make it look like someone fired the arrow from outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.61,0:11:57.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't think that trick would work...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.74,0:12:02.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It does work! After all, I just fired it the same way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.99,0:12:07.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? The trick I used is still in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.83,0:12:09.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.54,0:12:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in my case, immediately afterwards, an arrow was also fired into the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.80,0:12:17.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That trick was also simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.26,0:12:22.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You stapled a string with a weight attached above the bathroom window,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.47,0:12:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,passing the remaining string between the pillars above, and to hold it in place
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.10,0:12:28.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you just caught it beneath the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.27,0:12:31.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then by just opening the window the string would be released,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.36,0:12:34.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the bathroom glass beneath would break.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.78,0:12:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before that, Tanaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had already fired an arrow at the bathroom mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.74,0:12:44.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, Tanaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, when Ran and co. went to the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.54,0:12:48.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you took the chance to get rid of the objects you used.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.08,0:12:54.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As proof of this, back then I found a staple, as well as the hole it made outside the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.75,0:12:58.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what about the bow-gun we found in the woods?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.22,0:13:01.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because when you went outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.72,0:13:07.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you dropped it while making everyone focus on the footprints there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.60,0:13:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was then, right?\NThat you pulled the arrow from the tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.31,0:13:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The arrow used to move Hamano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the one with a hole on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.90,0:13:22.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Back then, it looked like you slipped and fell, {'and landed on your ass', but let's avoid overly strong swearing on a deduction show}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.66,0:13:25.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it was actually the recoil from pulling out the arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.37,0:13:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.45,0:13:31.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could congratulate you on a brilliant deduction, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.46,0:13:35.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't have the time to kill Hamano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.09,0:13:38.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time, I was burning firewood for the bath,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.71,0:13:41.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it took about 8 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.59,0:13:46.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it impossible for me to have heated the bath {\i1}and{\i0} gone into Hamano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.97,0:13:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to commit this impossible crime in just eight minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.39,0:13:55.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you'd been warming the bath before, it's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:13:59.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? I was chosen to warm the bath by chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.07,0:14:02.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chance? That was no "chance."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.70,0:14:04.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.36,0:14:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd already been Hamano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s magic assistant once before,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.08,0:14:12.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so you already knew in advance what would happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.04,0:14:13.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.33,0:14:17.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd already prepared the papers with the symbols written on the back for the trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.88,0:14:19.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and kept them in your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.80,0:14:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "ignorant" assistant would write the names in the paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.13,0:14:25.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the magician would then "guess" the names.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.80,0:14:29.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But weren't you the one who wrote the marks back then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.77,0:14:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. My eyes were blindfolded,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.39,0:14:38.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I didn't know that Tanaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was giving me a pen with no ink!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.82,0:14:45.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically, I couldn't know the pen had no ink, and that the papers had been marked in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.11,0:14:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And everybody there believed I'd written them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.04,0:14:55.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, you suggested that magic trick to Hamano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.08,0:14:57.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,making sure you'd take care of the bath,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.17,0:15:00.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and climbing on the roof of the bath you'd already heated,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.05,0:15:02.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you entered the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.51,0:15:06.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finally, you waited in Hamano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room for him and strangled him,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.93,0:15:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then employed the trick to commit the so-called "impossible crime"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.31,0:15:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the thief that's been lurking around was Tanaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.10,0:15:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was probably checking the length of the string for the trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.36,0:15:23.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as well as the type of pen that's used in the lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.82,0:15:26.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you insist that much, do you have any proof?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.82,0:15:31.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you want proof? Look in your boots!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.99,0:15:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have the remaining arrow in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.33,0:15:41.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had a reason to ask Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} to run this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.59,0:15:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because I wanted you to come too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.97,0:15:53.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since until very recently, you didn't have the time to come this way to remove the arrow here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.02,0:15:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one left now is the one used for this demonstration,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.56,0:16:02.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which means you had no choice but to pull it out when we followed Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.94,0:16:07.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hole! There {\i1}is{\i0} an arrow mark here! {literally "There is a mark left by an arrow" but yeah}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.78,0:16:09.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.91,0:16:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you couldn't throw away an arrow you'd worked on around here,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.99,0:16:17.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,your boots were the best place to hide it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.04,0:16:21.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the Shadow Priest was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.79,0:16:26.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, that was an fake person created by Tanaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.17,0:16:29.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,using another person's ID.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.13,0:16:34.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she and the Shadow Priest were both in the chat at the same time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.77,0:16:40.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's possible if you have two phone lines, modems, and computers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.77,0:16:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, not just "Shadow Priest,"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.65,0:16:50.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the name "Kikue Tanaka" and its ID also belong to someone else, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.03,0:16:55.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.12,0:16:58.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They really belong to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.50,0:17:06.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The granddaughter of the man whose death you caused, Hūden Harui!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.46,0:17:10.09,Signs,,0,0,0,,- Hūden Harui's...\N- Granddaughter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.09,0:17:11.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could you be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.76,0:17:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.22,0:17:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great Grandfather used my ID to chat with you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.52,0:17:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the handle name "Fake Child." {ikasama dōji}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.31,0:17:27.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I learned of this when I went through Grandfather's things and found his chat logs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.69,0:17:30.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd thought it was weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.95,0:17:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he wouldn't stop talking about doing the escape magic, despite being weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.70,0:17:38.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.25,0:17:43.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Grandfather chose to do that trick himself and died trying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.75,0:17:47.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't blame you guys for his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.42,0:17:51.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But... what I couldn't forgive was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.01,0:17:56.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The comments Nishiyama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Hamano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} made about Grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.51,0:18:11.15,Signs,,0,0,0,,<Illusion> It's too bad what happened\Nto Hūden Harui{\rHonorifics - Signs}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.51,0:18:11.15,Signs,,0,0,0,,<RedHerring> Illusion: It really is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.52,0:18:11.15,Signs,,0,0,0,,<SilentVentriloquist> I read it in the paper too, what a surprise...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.52,0:18:11.15,Signs,,0,0,0,,<EscapeKing> Ehh, he's probably happy he died on-stage! lol
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.61,0:18:11.15,Signs,,0,0,0,,<DisappearingBunny> This is what they call "an old man's indiscretion," eh? (^^;)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.08,0:18:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.54,0:18:27.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he planned to reveal his identity to everyone once he'd succeeded at the escape magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.17,0:18:32.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Somehow, I still managed to do the escape trick. Did you enjoy it?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.26,0:18:37.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"From the Fake Child, Hūden Harui."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.05,0:18:43.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I saw those untransmitted comments, they made me so sad, so filled with regret...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.98,0:18:47.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't stop myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.90,0:18:54.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But... if those two knew that the Fake Child was Harui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, they wouldn't have...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.74,0:18:59.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... But {\i1}he{\i0} saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.53,0:19:00.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"He"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.95,0:19:02.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doitō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.66,0:19:07.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know because the day before the show, he sent my grandfather an encouraging email.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.79,0:19:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But... How did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.00,0:19:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably because he's a magician, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.51,0:19:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Haven't you figured it out yet?
